name: Galactic wreckage in Stephan's Quintet
description:
This portrait of Stephan's Quintet, also known as the Hickson Compact Group 92, was taken by the new Wide Field Camera 3 (WFC3) aboard the NASA/ESA Hubble Space Telescope. Stephan's Quintet, as the name implies, is a group of five galaxies. 

Name:	Hickson Compact Group 92, Stephan's Quintet
Type:	Local Universe : Galaxy : Grouping : Cluster
Distance:	300 million light years
Constellation:	Pegasus
Category:	Galaxies

3,629 editions for the known 3,629 planetary systems to date.

Credit: ESA/Hubble/NASA
